stanford learning organization web slow the stanford learning organization web slow is an informal network of stanford researchers staff and students along with colleagues and friends from the corporate world interested in the nature and development of learning organizations special note rumor has it that slow's founder dr james milojkovic deliberately coined our acronym so that members would be called slow learners this appellation has apparently provided a potent self selection mechanism resources all resources including recommended articles books and videos for reinventing organizational learning are now housed at http www knowledgepassion com last updated december 11 1999 comments send mail to dr james milojkovic
